Step 1 : Create the template
<div class="container" style="padding: 2rem">
    <h1>Careers at Our Restaurant</h1>
    <p>We're always looking for passionate, talented people to join our team.</p>

    <h3>Why Work with us></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Friendly and supportive environment</li>
        <li>Opportunities for growth and learning</li>
        <li>Delicious meals every day</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
       Interested? Email your resume to
       <a href="mailto:caareers@reataurant.com">careers@restaurant.com</a>.
    </p>
</div>

Step 2 : Create the view
from django.shortcuts import render

def careers(request):
    return render(request, 'careers.html')

Step 3 : Add URL Route
from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    #..other paths
    path('careers/', views.careers, nme='careers'),
]

Step 4 : Link it in navvigation
<li><a href="{% url 'careers' %}">Careers</a></li>

http://127.0.0.1:8000/careers/